    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>In a Heat Wave, an Opportunity</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Physicians for Social Responsibility president Dr Robert M Gould letter on Aug 18 article on changing weather patterns that have brought mosquito proliferation and West Nile virus to Colorado urges efforts to prevent predicted health effects of global warming; drawing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Spring Rains and Summer Heat Bring West Nile Virus to Colorado'' (front page, Aug. 18):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Spring Rains and Summer Heat Bring West Nile Virus to Colorado'' (front page, Aug. 18):</p>
        <p>The changing weather patterns conducive to mosquito proliferation and the spread of the West Nile virus are consistent with predictions issued in reports by the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change regarding potential impacts of global warming on infectious disease.</p>
        <p>Beyond using appropriate mosquito abatement and public health measures, it is critical for health officials to advocate for aggressive efforts by our government to curb greenhouse gas emissions to prevent the anticipated health effects of climate change.</p>
        <p>ROBERT M. GOULD, M.D.  President  Physicians for Social Responsibility  San Francisco, Aug. 18, 2003</p>
      </block>
